column3: RIGHT LUNG ( RESECTION ) : INFILTRRTING MODERATELY WELL EFFERENTIATED KERATINIZING SQUAMOUS CARCINOMA .
THE CARCINOMA EASURES 2.5 CM IN GREATEST DIMENSION AND EXTENDS TO INVOLVE THE
CARCINOMA IN TWO ( 2 ) OF EIGHTEEN ( 18 ) PERIBRONCHIAL LYMPH DUES .
BRONCHIAL AND PLEURAL MARGINS NEGATIVE FOR TUMOR .
LYMPH NODE LEVEL 7 ( BX ) : ONE ( 1 ) LYMPH NODE NEGATIVE FOR TUMOR .
DTE : We do not identify an in situ component to the carcinoma in the ung .
While this is consistent with a metastasis of the patient 's ongue primary a primary lung carcinoma can not be ruled out .
